topic.title: Fopnu1.53 , Ipv6 based peer 2 peer downloading tool
topic.body:
Take a look
https://ibb.co/xzjNrfb

[official fopnu com](http://www.fopnu.com)


Fopnu is far better than the rest:

Simple and easy to use
Fully decentralized network
All shared files are indexed locally
No relaying of other user's searches
Pure UDP protocol that utilizes forward error correction
Full connection encryption and decentralized public key infrastructure
Recirculating token system that helps distribute upload bandwidth fairly
Efficient and fast transfers via re-combining and re-encoding blocks at all nodes
Clean install and uninstall, or stand-alone operation, with no annoying .Net or Java dependencies
NO Spyware   NO Ads    NO Nonsense

> [zenanon](#comment_97_14kTJXu4KZSoWSSNcGtXEijf4NqEGimc9J): My only issue with Tox is that it uses direct ip connections between peers (or did last time I've used it), so it basically leaks a person's identity.

You should try latern or shadowsocks mate .Set out the prefix proxy .

> [zenanon](#comment_99_14kTJXu4KZSoWSSNcGtXEijf4NqEGimc9J): I've used SocksCap in the past to force apps to use Tor. Not an expert on that stuff though.

sockscap is dead and don't use it for anony connect.

> [zenanon](#comment_100_14kTJXu4KZSoWSSNcGtXEijf4NqEGimc9J): Yeah it has been a while since I've messed with it. Too bad since I trust the Tor network more than some other things that are out there. An app which just pipes data through Tor seems more secure than some app that uses it's own homebrew method. Same thinking about VPN providers, just don't trust them.

VPN will be good for tunel the TOR traffic.
